first of all, when you walk in it makes you feel like you've just stumbled into a bar that frodo and the gang would have stopped in on their journey to mordor. from the dark atmosphere, the brick interior and the fireplaces, i feel like it's a cozy pub right outside of the shire. &nbsp;this place is definitely my favorite for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. the blood orange whiskey sour is where it's at, also their moscow mules are pretty killer as well. now, let's talk about their food. the mac &amp; cheese is to die for. seriously i know this is a bar but their food is great. i also love their tomato bisque, fried pickles and everything else that's vegetarian friendly on the menu. the staff is super friendly and helpful. i've never had a bad experience. this place can get super packed on the weekends but the street parking isn't too terrible. also remember that they don't let sports team logos on any of your attire, they made my boyfriend drop his la kings hat off in the car before he was allowed in.
i just had a farewell shindig here last night and it was the perfect venue for a small get together of about 20-30 people. &nbsp;the bartender with the nose piercing was super cool and cute btw -- wish i had gotten her name! &nbsp;she was very attentive, friendly and provided excellent customer service. :) they have large seating areas with small tables centered around a fireplace that was just the right size for me and my friends. &nbsp;it was great because most of my friends came early for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> and it wasn't crowded at all. &nbsp;but later on after about 11pm the place got pretty busy. &nbsp;however, the bouncer is good about not letting the place get too packed and would only allow people in as others exited so it was still quite comfortable inside. &nbsp;all in all, i had a great time and a wonderful experience at the griffin and i highly recommend it to anyone who's looking for a chill bar in the los feliz/atwater village area.
