this place was a bit of a drive from where i live but i've heard rave reviews so i had to try it out. i am soooo glad i did, this place is amazing! you would never think that a place that serves such amazing gourmet burgers would be in a little strip mall in glendale, but it is worth the hype. i came on a tuesday night so it wasn't that busy and i had no wait at all. everything looked so good and i couldn't decide so my waitress (maren i think it was?) suggested the &quot;rehab&quot; burger which had all sorts of goodies, and a side of truffle fries. omg i have to give it up to her that was an excellent choice. she also let us know they have a great <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> from 3-6 on weekdays so we will definitely be coming back for that. also i don't know why there are bad reviews about the service and decor.. i thought it was a+. friendly servers and great food, what more could you ask for?!
eden burger bar is bizarre and feels like you are eating at some cheap replica of a vegas lounge complete with the second-hand smoke of patrons who smoke by the doorway. and i thought glendale was supposed to be implementing their &quot;fresh air ordinance&quot;. so yes, aside from the interestingly awkward interior design theme consisting of cushioned furniture and awkward chandeliers colored with the hues of purple, gray, and black, they seem to be really stingy with their air conditioning because it was not on. perhaps they think that by making people hot, they will drink more. wrong!you see, i have a hard time drinking beer when it's hot and stuffy like balls in a hipster's skinny jeans. because when you are hot temperature-wise, studies have shown that you tend to get angrier. if it was cooler inside, then i might have had a &quot;cooler&quot; experience. food-wise they offer decent burgers that are $10+ for the burger alone. they have a set number of burgers that are uncustomizable &quot;sang yoon-style&quot; that include exotic meats such as boar, duck, and lamb. but if you are looking for a good old-fashioned burger you may need to build it yourself. the wife and i just got the blue, which was a burger with bleu cheese. the pizza that we had was pretty tasty (we had the vino consisting of &nbsp;cheese with balsamic glaze) and averaged $10+ and the beers were decently priced since the owner owns the adjoining eden wine &amp; spirits liquor store. draft beer wise they have about 7-8 and the rest are all bottled. if you order a bottled beer you may see the server disappear down the connecting hallway to get the beer from the liquor store. lol. at the end of the day, the interior furniture combined with the lack of air flow and cigarette smoke made the whole place feel stuffy and uncomfortable. moreover, the absence of a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> made me an even more unhappy drinker.link to hot temperatures and hot tempers: <a href="/redir?url=