the d&eacute;cor is a little over the top, but the burger was really good.don't get me wrong. &nbsp;i love purple, but it reminds me of a nightclub with the sofas upholstered in purple velvet and the white vinyl chairs.food: &nbsp;4/5 starsdrinks:$2.00 for a mini soda bottle (no refills). &nbsp;my husband asked if he could have a grown up version. &nbsp;nah.....i guess not. &nbsp;$3.00 for an ice tea. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.yelp.com/user_local_photos?userid=o8lo2pvm19nyypbbycgsvg">yelp.com/user_local_phot…</a>burgers etc.:hamburgers: &nbsp;i ordered the fig burger $12.00. &nbsp;not sure if i could figure out where the figs were, but i like the sundried tomatoes and gouda cheese. the ground beef was really tasty and reminded me of some really good homemade burgers. <a href="http://www.yelp.com/user_local_photos?select=gsmxa12ige106bh1hhlneq&amp;userid=o8lo2pvm19nyypbbycgsvg">yelp.com/user_local_phot…</a>my son ordered the firehouse for $10.00. &nbsp;he ate a couple bites, but i think it was a little too fancy for him. &nbsp; i did see people ordering some pizzas and they looked like new york style with a nice looking crust. &nbsp; i also saw a few kids while we were there, so i'll edit the business info which indicated that it isn't good for kids. &nbsp;i don't agree with that, especially at lunch time.my hubby liked the hot wings ($10.00 for 8.00). &nbsp;the truffle fries were very good. &nbsp; prices seemed a little steep at $44.00 for three of us and no alcholoic beverages, but maybe they have a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> deal. &nbsp;i looked on their website and could not determine if they do or not, so i would recommend calling.service: &nbsp;4/5 starsdezy was our server and she was good. &nbsp;she was new and wasn't too sure if they had any different breads like sourdough for the pastrami since my hubby doesn't like rye. &nbsp;no, they just have marble and rye.atmosphere: 3/5 starsi prefer a casual atmosphere for a burger joint with some windows or a nice relaxing patio. &nbsp;they had some tables outside, but they are right on a busy street, so i wouldn't sit out there. &nbsp; the purple velvet sofas were a little long in the seat, so if you have shorter legs you might be uncomfortable. &nbsp;i sat in the white vinyl chair facing the sofa and then felt like i couldn't look around the room because i was facing the wall. parking: 4/5 starsit's a strip mall, so there is plenty of free parking.recommendation:i'd definitely go back again for lunch. &nbsp;i have a feeling it gets a little crowded in the evening based upon some of the other reviews i've read.
very sexy. &nbsp;purple velvet &amp; white leather fabrics, gray-lined walls, white bar, chandeliers, and strikingly hot and tattooey servers...that's what i'm talking about. &nbsp;little did i know, that this relatively hidden place in glendale would enter into the &quot;top 5&quot; of my &quot;berger knows burgers&quot; list. &nbsp;burgers, salads, pizzas, drafts...yep, life is good. &nbsp;that is, if you even dare to come in.outside, a little down and out...and you might just pass on by and not care to even go in. &nbsp;an older storefront, in fact, the whole little center of shops looks like a an old hacienda on a film set in mexico -- but don't be fooled. &nbsp;it's a trip to a vegas lounge inside. &nbsp;pssst - they close at midnight, too...you can order a burger at 1145pm if you want! &nbsp; plus, <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> drink specials 3pm-6pm.good menu! &nbsp;a lamb burger, 8-10 beef burger choices ($10), veggie burgers, pastrami burger. &nbsp;lots of good options, salads, and the pizzas look like a must-try, too.1. &nbsp;buffalo-style burger ($12) -- a special, 35 day-aged beef (8 oz), brioche bun, buffalo-style sauce (mild), blue cheese, avocado, bacon...whoa baby, that's what i like. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/eden-burger-bar-glendale?select=58h2ehvn3ij4jeu95n5yza#xfo5m_bdooowvqmp-mwxua">yelp.com/biz_photos/eden…</a>2. &nbsp;truffle fries ($4) - long, shoestring, tossed in truffle oil. &nbsp;excellent flavor, and really liked the texture...which stayed crisp even 20-30 mins into eating. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/eden-burger-bar-glendale?select=58h2ehvn3ij4jeu95n5yza#58h2ehvn3ij4jeu95n5yza">yelp.com/biz_photos/eden…</a>3. &nbsp;onion rings ($4) - absolutely delish. &nbsp;the onion tasted caramelized, soft, easy to bite thru. &nbsp;the batter, not too thin, not too thick -- they're jjjuuuussst right. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/eden-burger-bar-glendale?select=58h2ehvn3ij4jeu95n5yza#amfs8nrpzye2uao3vzj_ew">yelp.com/biz_photos/eden…</a>4. &nbsp;macaroons ($6 for 3) - changes daily, but i shared the salted caramel, orange chocolate, and pistachio. &nbsp;their served a bit chilled, so the consistency was a little different for each. &nbsp;tasty morsels, for sure, but best to get direct from a bakery (or bottega louie). will i be back? &nbsp;hell yeah. &nbsp;do i want to try everything on the menu? &nbsp;hell yeah. &nbsp;next up: &quot;firehouse&quot; burger, which is jalapeno everything (jalapeno cheese, jalapeno bacon, etc). &nbsp;berger likes it spicy. &nbsp;speaking of...kerry, waitress/server/bartender/writer/hottie is super fun. &nbsp;she's a temptress. &nbsp;a great looking gal with a personality on steroids. &nbsp;like totally on fire cute. &nbsp;like i need another reason to come to this garden of eden? &nbsp;okay, that would be willow!
