(dined 10/21/13 m @ 4:00pm): this wine bar left me coasting towards a calming state - but where's the gallery!?a coworker and i returned to town after an afternoon offsite event just in time for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, so i recommended the left coast wine bar &amp; gallery - because a glass (or two) of wine sounded nice, and i remembered they had outdoor seating to enjoy this lovely weather.we actually arrived too early so we killed some time in the nearby bevmo! until the doors opened. we casually walked across the street, parked ourselves at a tall table out on the front patio and allowed the rest of the day to sweep us away with good conversation, libations, and snacks at discounted prices. here was how our happiest of <span class="highlighted">hours</span> went: &nbsp;sangria ($5.00 ea. hh) - this deep red elixir with minute chunks of various fruit was the perfect prescription for a warm california fall afternoon. our bulbous glasses (two each) were filled to the rim as each sip elicited a smile and a relaxed state of being. although the potency was minimal, the results were a resounding positive vibe. <a href="http://www.yelp.com/user_local_photos?userid=8jvt2inwc8giq6sh2ug9vw">yelp.com/user_local_phot…</a> left coast pizza ($8.99 hh) - this round flatbread personal-sized pizza was drizzled with fresh herbs and olive oil, mozzarella cheese, diced tomatoes, chopped onions, pasilla peppers, and prosciutto. i enjoyed the crunchiness of the excess melted cheese that extended past the crust. the saltiness of the prosciutto somehow seemed amplified, but the rest of the ingredients aided in dampening this effect. however, i felt this was a bit overcooked as the cheese had several dark spots throughout, yet the vegetables still remained fresh and juicy. my only suggestion was to increase the size maybe one more inch in diameter. <a href="http://www.yelp.com/user_local_photos?select=smxrqq3n-qzqngdky7mhjq&amp;userid=8jvt2inwc8giq6sh2ug9vw">yelp.com/user_local_phot…</a>service - our server was a friendly attractive woman by the name of rachelle. the place had just opened so we chose wherever we wanted to sit (outside on this beautifully warm day). she immediately greeted us with both standard and <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menus. we quickly placed our drink order and soon enough received them, at which time we then placed our food order, which unfortunately took longer than expected - since there were only two other small parties. we ordered a second round of drinks which again came quickly. lastly, the check was delivered once requested. overall, things were good.parking - there was metered street parking along the main drag of harvard st. otherwise, we parked in the nearby parking structure on maryland ave. where the first 90 minutes are free, then $1.00 for every 30 minutes after that (we paid $3.00).atmosphere, d&eacute;cor, ambience - there was a nice front outdoor patio with umbrellas and heating lamps if necessary. inside, it was a bit narrow and tight with several tables and chairs along with stools at the bar. there was a slightly roomier upstairs lounge area with couches, chairs, tables, and paintings hung on the walls, where live entertainment occurred on a nightly basis. generally, the walls were a dark color, and there was plenty of both electric and natural lighting. i didn't recall any tvs nor background music. however, the street traffic can be annoying as you're very close to the americana on brand. a real chill place. attire - it was totally casual so i would normally be in a t-shirt, boardshorts, and flip-flops.overall, left coast wine bar &amp; gallery was a nice wine option in glendale as there were so few of them. they had a decent selection of wines and beers with comparable prices. their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu was limited as well as their general food selection. <a href="http://www.yelp.com/user_local_photos?select=_c4gl9sscrzva-5lod3npa&amp;userid=8jvt2inwc8giq6sh2ug9vw">yelp.com/user_local_phot…</a> i'd come back simply for a drink or two while i hung with friends and caught up. i found very good value based on the prices, service, and experience noted above (total experience was around $35.00 before tip), and a nice place to chill with your drinks and hopefully some live music if you're here in the evening. and, they accepted my credit card of choice...amex!
