this place is the perfect if you're looking for a calm place to spend friday night. &nbsp;the best time to go is right when it opens at 8pm... staying as long as you like of course. &nbsp;it does start to fill up around 11, like most places. the bartenders and owner are so friendly and <span class="highlighted">happy</span> to be running their own business the way they want to run it. &nbsp;you can see it everything they do. &nbsp;specialty beer rotates through the taps and tasting is encouraged. &nbsp;they have also grandfathered one of two existing licenses allowing them to sell alcohol to go. &nbsp;the only other operating bar with the same license is incidentally another great bar, the golden gopher. &nbsp;after talking with the owner for over an <span class="highlighted">hour</span>, sampling cherry beer! white belgians! and ipas, he suggested a japanese white belgian to take home with me. &nbsp;so good, really. they also have a back smoking patio and plenty of space for big groups so you'll never feel cramped here. &nbsp;also, for some reason, their bathrooms are absolutely gorgeous (?) &nbsp; the first time i came i had the hardest time finding it as it is located in a very residential area and also because i arrived like, 30 minutes before it opened on opening day. &nbsp; a little bit over-eager, perhaps?
