verdugo, i love you. you're a little easy to miss (only a nondescript &quot;cocktails&quot; sign out front) on this non-nightlife-y glassell park stretch and can seem shady from the outside, but you never fail to brighten my week. verdugo's down the street from a park, and its neighbors are an apartment complex and a weird, fenced-in place (my buddies and i still haven't figured out what it does) that seems to do business at odd <span class="highlighted">hours</span>. slightly shady surroundings aside, the bar's interior includes a darkly lit but cute, tiny lounge area with limited seating and prohibition-era decor; another room with more seating; and my <span class="highlighted">happy</span> place: the big, badass patio area with picnic tables where people can play r-rated jenga. the vibe's chill, the beats are cool (sometimes djs will spin at night) and the bartenders are friendly/entertaining (big-ups to katie and wes!). it's a mostly hipster vibe but i've had no problems talking to all kinds of people here. my only gripes are that there's only one stall in the women's room and that it's sometimes tricky to get a drink when the place gets packed on certain nights (hence the 4 stars instead of 5). but the beers they have on tap, which change periodically, make it worth it. cocktails are good as well and sometimes you benefit from a random heavy-handed pour, wink wink. come thirsty, leave <span class="highlighted">happy</span>.
