i brought my wife here to celebrate her birthday. &nbsp;since we had decided on &quot;dinner and a movie&quot; for her bday, we decided to share an appetizer and entree (cuz' we knew we were going to get some popcorn and soda at the movies).as soon as we were seated (and greeted) we received two glasses of water and a small bowl of popcorn drizzled with duck fat. &nbsp;i was surprised at how much duck fat tasted like real, salted butter. &nbsp;it was a nice change of pace from bread and butter, biscuits or chips and salsa being brought out prior to the meal. &nbsp;my only complaint would be that they drizzled a little too much duck fat on our popcorn, leaving an unappealing pool of grease which the pieces of popcorn at the bottom sat in.since we arrived during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, we took advantage of the $7.00 appetizer offering; we went with the fried pork belly bites served with and herb creme fraiche. the pork belly bites were very reminiscent of mexican carniceria (meat market) style chicharones (pork rinds). &nbsp;they are crispy and crunchy, salty and meaty, and are most definitely fried. &nbsp;i wasn't a fan of the seasoning on them (which i perceived as a heavy clove like flavor) but the herb creme fraiche (a mild, watery like sour cream) cut through it nicely.we ordered the buffalo burger which is billed as follows: all natural grass fed buffalo, portabello mushrooms, roasted red onions, gruyere cheese, wild arugula &amp; garlic aioli. &nbsp;since we split the burger, the burger was served, freshly cut in half, with each of us getting a generous side of fries on our plate (very nice touch). &nbsp;the burger was juicy and thick. &nbsp;the combination of toppings with the burger was tasty, as were the side of fries.when taking our orders, i asked the waitress to please bring out the beer i ordered with the burger. &nbsp;although a different waiter/server brought us our entrees, she was quick behind him with my beer. now that's great service. &nbsp;my wife only wanted water, but our waitress didn't neglect her because she did; her glass was always politely refilled. this is a nice, neat little gastropub in the chino area. &nbsp;it definitely has its locals, which tend to cozy up at the bar, but none of them seemed to be overly &quot;annoying&quot; in that &quot;hey, this is my bar, so i do what i want&quot; kind of way.overall, it was a great experience for a &quot;date night&quot; with the wife. next time we can find a night away from the children for one, i think we'll start it here again.
