they treat <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> guests like shit. if you're ordering food off the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu but not having &quot;dinner,&quot; you're only allowed to sit at the bar. there were tons of open tables, but we were supposed to stand around and wait for a seat at the bar, which was full. oftentimes, <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> bleeds into dinner, and i will end up spending the bucks. if you're not going to seat me when you have so many open tables, i'm not going to stick around. why even bother having a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> if you're only going to be nice to people paying non-<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> prices?
