3 1/2 stars. came here for the first time to watch a game and for some <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> food. there is street parking and valet for $3.00. the inside is cozy and hip. more of a sit down and restaurant feel. the upstairs is way more of a bar and sports bar feel. lot's of big tv for games, a bar, and couple of high tables and chairs. it's pretty dark upstairs. and it can get a bit stuffy when it gets crowded. the second time i came here was for my girlfriends birthday. it happened to be the same day as the king's win the stanley cup, woot woot!! so you can say it was pretty packed. i was pretty hungry so my gf and i just went down to get some actual dinner instead of finger foods. although the food is just okay it is great for drinks, watching the game and <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> bar food._avocado fries. pretty good. nothing great. i personally like my avocados non fried but this was good with the cool lime aioli dip. good to get for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>._pan seared crab cakes. got this from raved reviews for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. it was horrible! worst crab cakes ever! maybe it was that day but wow. the crab cake was extremely salty and mushy. tasted like it was still a raw and they were getting ready to fry it. had to return as it was just uneatable. _heirloom tomato &amp; burrata. this was just okay. the tomato was not that fresh and in overall it just tasted like something you could have easily made at home._f yeah fries. this was a bit too rich and cheesy for me. the fries were smothered in cheese so it got soggy pretty quick. _crispy buttermilk fried chicken ($17) bacon slaw, naughty &amp; nice sauce. this was a great entree. the fried chicken was moist, nicely fried and comes in 4 big pieces. the slaw was just okay. a bit too much dressing. but the sauce which was some blueberry preserve was amazing!!! simple yet tasted so great with the chicken. a tad sweet but not overpowering. i used that sauce with everything! a little overpriced but damn that sauce was well worth it. _fried chicken sandwich ($13) breaded white meat, bacon coleslaw, best relish ever. this was just soso. i expected it to be great from reviews and although the chicken itself was great the bread was a miss. it was soggy and did not have that nice toasted crunch. in the end i just took out the chicken and dipped it in that amazing sauce. overall i would come here for drinks and just to spend time with friends but not really for a great dining experience. although i would come back to get the fried chicken and amazing sauce and maybe try some other things off the menu.
