i've lived across the street from hyperion public for a year now and in that time i've consistently been pleasantly surprised by their food, drinks and atmosphere. adding a killer <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> was a great move and i've definitely been going there a lot more since that addition. their wings are amongst the best i've had in los angeles, the f yeah fries are fantastic and i love their salads. i also like that their brunch menu has a good variety of both breakfast and lunch foods, not just eggs 100 different ways like so many brunch spots in the area. sitting outside on the patio past the restaurant and smoking deck is lovely, but be prepared to have compromised service if that's where you chose to sit.
***3.5 stars***i went here for dinner and <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> on a tuesday night. hp is super cute with benches and open windows. i love the look and feel of the place. i had a beer (some type of white ale and i loved it) and the turkey meatloaf dish. it was $10 tuesday so my turkey was only $10. it looked really good on the plate and was served with brussels sprout petals and i believe cauliflower puree. i loved the puree and sprout petals, although they really should of put more veg to balance out the meatloaf. the meatloaf was tasty and lean (no grease), however, it was very very salty (the gouda contributed to this). they also put sriracha aioli sauce on the side and even though it was good, i just felt like there was too much going on with this dish. if it was less salty, i would of been even happier. portion wise, it was huge. i ate half and ate the other half for lunch the next day. onto the service--it was excellent. everyone was super friendly and attentive. i'll be back since it's a good <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> spot. there's street parking but that fills up fast so there's always free valet and you just have to tip the guy.
my favorite part of hyperion public is their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> sliders. i also like the smoking patio. otherwise, i could take it or leave it. i find it to be inconsistent. take the truffle mac 'n cheese for example -- the first time i tried it i was blown away. the flavor and texture were spot on. nice, not overwhelming, truffle flavor with a crunchy top and creamy middle. second time i ordered it? almost inedible: watery, brown, grainy and with an overpowering truffle flavor. i'd love to order the first one again, but i really don't want to wind up with the second time one. sliders are really good, and so are the sesame wings. not a fan of their signature cocktails. haven't had one i like. i live close by so i will probably continue to go. hopefully they can work out the inconsistent kitchen kinks.
