came here on a wednesday night and ordered two orders of the crab cakes, the turkey sliders, and the lettuce cups off the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu.the crab cakes were the best in our opinion. two come in an order and they were soft and not dry. the sauce that comes with it was a nice touch to add a creamy note to the savory and sweet flavors of the crab meat and spices. the turkey sliders were a disappointment. the hawaiian bread they used was alright but the turkey meat was dry and overall it almost felt reminiscent to what i could've have gotten out of a frozen dinner.the lettuce cups were pretty good. the first bite was full of flavor, but that might have been a little of a problem. because there were so many flavors in the marinade of the meat and the mixture of sauces, it felt a bit overpowering by the second bite. that said however, i still finished the lettuce cup with ease after taking bites of our other orders. my friend also ordered the whiskey sour. verdict was that it was pretty good, but not as strong as expected.now the best part of the night was that after a while, we were told that bingo was about to start. we ended up playing a few rounds and won some ridiculous prizes. so if you're going to go to the bar, go on wednesday night. the guys working there are a lot of fun and friendly. overall, we had a really good time and chilling, talking, and playing games.
eat at home. 5 stars as a pub -- <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is good, beers are reasonably priced with a good selection, and the cocktails aren't going to break the bank. the scene is solid, decor is good, and enough tv's to watch a game without it being too overwhelming. 1 star as a restaurant -- seems like they're going for indulgence/sloppy salty greasy comfort food. with the exception of the homemade potato chips, i have yet to get a meal here that is anything better than mediocre. that whole sloppy/salty/greasy thing can be done well, but you just end up with a bland mess that screws up your stomach without the satisfaction of real comfort food. so yeah -- eat at home or any of the other restaurants in the area, then head there for a beer at their excellent pub.
