i have been here several times and each time i love it a little bit more. &nbsp;first of all, it is such a great addition to the neighborhood! &nbsp;i love all the other local places too, but this definitely fills its own niche. &nbsp;first, i fell in love with the space. &nbsp;it's a huge open space with several different kinds of seating arrangements, open to the street and with a great big cozy fireplace. &nbsp;then, i fell in love with the food. &nbsp;being vegetarian, there are lots of things i can't try, but i don't ever feel left out. &nbsp;the mac and cheese is seriously the best i've ever had, and the veggie items in the deli case are fresh and delightfully varied. &nbsp;i've brought several items to various events (picnic, potluck) to rave reviews. &nbsp;coffee is great too! &nbsp;and, since they got their liquor license, i am also fond of coming here for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, and they have wonderful meat/cheese plate options to enjoy with your wine! &nbsp;my favorite thing to do for lunch is pick a few different things from the deli case to make my own little tapas collection. &nbsp;they will even arrange it all together on one place, warming what needs to be heated, and bring it to me. &nbsp;i'm always surprised when i do this at how truly reasonably priced it comes out to be! &nbsp;for example, a friend and i each had lovely specialty coffees (cappuccino/latte), three quesadilla triangles with sour cream and salsa, a quinoa patty with some kind of delicious chipotle pepper cream sauce, two veggie dolmas, and three little pastries stuffed with various meat/chicken salads (for my friend). &nbsp;it was all served beautifully on a big plate and it was less than $20, and that was before my kcrw 15% discount! &nbsp;we both had plenty to eat and got to enjoy the wonderful ambience of this friendly neighborhood place. &nbsp;highly recommend!
